To use the R6 class for training with a specified set of parameters or default parameters, you can control the configuration by passing arguments in the train_model method or by modifying the config.yaml file.

Here’s how:

1. Training with Specified Parameters

If you want to train with specific parameters:

Steps:

	1.	Update the config.yaml file or directly pass the parameters in your R6 method for training.
	2.	Set cv_number = 1 to skip cross-validation and use the specified parameters.

Example in Code:

If you want to set specific parameters for training, include them in the tuneGrid section of the config.yaml file:

modeling:
  training:
    cross_validation:
      tune_grid:
        nrounds: [100] # Fixed parameter
        max_depth: [6] # Fixed parameter
        eta: [0.03]    # Fixed parameter
        gamma: [0.1]   # Fixed parameter
        colsample_bytree: [0.8] # Fixed parameter
        min_child_weight: [1]   # Fixed parameter
        subsample: [0.9]        # Fixed parameter

Then call:

claims_model$train_model(number_cv = 1)

The model will train with exactly these parameters.

2. Training with Default Parameters

If you want to train with default parameters:

Steps:

	1.	Leave the tune_grid empty or remove it from the config.yaml file.
	2.	Modify the train_model method to use default parameters if none are specified.

Example in Code:

Default parameters in config.yaml:

modeling:
  training:
    cross_validation:
      tune_grid: null # Or leave this section blank

In your R6 class, check if the tune_grid is null or empty and use default parameters:

setup_tune_grid = function() {
  if (is.null(self$config$modeling$training$cross_validation$tune_grid)) {
    # Use default parameters if none are specified
    self$tune_grid <- expand.grid(
      nrounds = 100,
      max_depth = 6,
      eta = 0.03,
      gamma = 0.1,
      colsample_bytree = 0.8,
      min_child_weight = 1,
      subsample = 0.9
    )
  } else {
    # Use parameters from config.yaml
    self$tune_grid <- expand.grid(
      nrounds = self$config$modeling$training$cross_validation$tune_grid$nrounds,
      max_depth = self$config$modeling$training$cross_validation$tune_grid$max_depth,
      eta = self$config$modeling$training$cross_validation$tune_grid$eta,
      gamma = self$config$modeling$training$cross_validation$tune_grid$gamma,
      colsample_bytree = self$config$modeling$training$cross_validation$tune_grid$colsample_bytree,
      min_child_weight = self$config$modeling$training$cross_validation$tune_grid$min_child_weight,
      subsample = self$config$modeling$training$cross_validation$tune_grid$subsample
    )
  }
}

Then call:

claims_model$train_model(number_cv = 1)

If the tune_grid is not defined in config.yaml, the model will fall back to default parameters.

Summary

	1.	To Train with Specific Parameters:
	•	Define parameters in config.yaml under tune_grid.
	•	Call train_model(number_cv = 1).
	2.	To Train with Default Parameters:
	•	Leave tune_grid in config.yaml blank or null.
	•	The class will automatically fall back to hardcoded default parameters.

